author: @neofx645
text: For anyone having problems loading your page after installing crispy here is a fix: The bootstrap 4 template pack isnt included in the django-crispy-forms package any more so you have to install it seperately. In the n the terminal type: pip install crispy-bootstrap4 At the bottom of the settings file, add the line: CRISPY_ALLOWED_TEMPLATE_PACKS = "bootstrap4" then add 'crispy_bootstrap4', to the installed apps.  But dont delete the crispy form stuff from the video, you need both of these.  üëçüëçüëçüëç

author: @vladinstein
text: If anyone is doing this tutorial and having troubles with crispy forms, with the help of tutorial and some comments, I found that this works:  1) pip install django_crispy_forms 2) pip install crispy_bootstrap4 3) Add both of these to INSTALLED_APPS:     'crispy_forms',     'crispy_bootstrap4', 4) Add both of these at the bottom: CRISPY_ALLOWED_TEMPLATE_PACKS = "bootstrap4"  CRISPY_TEMPLATE_PACK = 'bootstrap4' 5) Use {% load crispy_forms_tags %} and {{ form|crispy }} in the html file.  As always, great tutorial, thank you, Corey!

author: @riadshalahinleon349
text: People can get this kinda problem :  "Using the URLconf defined in django_project.urls, Django tried these URL patterns, in this order: admin/ register/ [name='register'] [name='blog-home'] about/ [name='blog-about'] The current path, register/index.html, didn't match any of these." ________________________  The problem is your form has action="Post", which is causing the browser to access a URL that doesn't exist.  You should use method="post" to get the brower to use a POST request for the form. use this (<form method="post">)  instead of this (<form action="Post">)

author: @heisenburgfreed7591
text:
If anyone wants to bootstrap-style specific form fields while still enjoying the convenience of the cripy forms, such as resizing, changing field's color and backgroud color, here is a great solution: Let me introduce a python package called ""django-widget-tweaks" Offical Website Documentation: https://pypi.org/project/django-widget-tweaks/ Steps: 1. intall the package using "pip install django-widget-tweaks" (strongly suggest to install under your virtual environment); 2. open settings.py in the django_project (your main project) folder; 3. add 'widget_tweaks', into the INSTALLED_APPS list block, in order to register the app, don't forget the COMMA at the end of the line; 4. open the template file, in this tutorial, the register.html under users/templates/users/; 5. add {% load widget_tweaks %} at the top of the register.html; 6. replace the {{ form|crispy }} with the below code block (Note: in the field|add_class:"add any bootstrap css names, use white-space between css names" ):
{% for field in form %}
{{ field|add_class:"form-control-sm border-0 rounded bg-dark text-light shadow-sm"|as_crispy_field }}
{% endfor %}
7. now the only thing left is to search the bootstrap documentation to find out right css style name you need via below official website link: i.e. if you want to change the field background and text colors, I could pick any css names in the link: https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.1/utilities/colors/ 8. save template and type command "python manage.py runserver" and use the browser to check and tune your customized bootstrap css styles. Love Corey's tutorial, probably the best free tutorial with very practical methods and very comprehensive explanation. Have a nice day!

text: Hi for those who have a problemes in debuggin run this instruction before (python manage.py runserver)    Install Dependencies  1 (pip install -r requirements.txt)   Set Database (Make Sure you are in directory same as manage.py)    2 (pip install pillow)  3 (python manage.py makemigrations) 4 (python manage.py migrate)   Create SuperUser  5 (python manage.py createsuperuser)     After all these steps , you can start testing and developing this project.   6( python manage.py runserver)    That's it! Happy Coding!

author: @rdacles08
text: Hello  @corey i just found out that when you register you can use email that is already in database. i found a solution to this if some one is looking for anwer. might not be the best. but it helps   add this code  below Email = forms.EmailField()  and Above class Meta:       def clean_email(self):         email = self.cleaned_data.get('email')         username = self.cleaned_data.get('username')         if email and User.objects.filter(email=email).exclude(username=username).exists():             raise forms.ValidationError(u'Email addresse is already  use.')         return email
